social_posts.post_text: With that, the 2022 season comes to an end- & what a year it was! Endless adventures in Italy, capped off with the wedding of the century. 3 weeks rafting the Grand Canyon. Backpacking the San Juans. I am hopelessly indecisive when it comes to picking clips & this audio is too short, so I only managed to capture Italy here. Thanks to all who played a part in a very special year, big or small. Grateful for all of you, but especially you Kels- te amo mi amor!

Mt Rainier in all its glory. I’ve seen this magical mountain from its icy slopes, and looked down into its glowing blue depths as I carefully placed my crampons on ladder rungs to cross its daunting crevasses- but I’ve NEVER seen it from this perspective as it’s usually shrouded in constant Pacific Northwest grey skies and cloud cover. I was flying home to Colorado after my grandfather’s funeral, remembering how he loved to tell his friends any chance he could that I’d climbed Rainier not once, but twice. Maybe he was letting me get a good look at it from his perspective now. Thanks gramps.
.
#mtrainier #seattle #washington #pnw

It’s a beautiful day… laying in bed filled with gratitude for this extraordinary life. For getting to share it with my best friend. For the spectacular souls I’ve met along the way. Has there been pain? Yes, but there’s been so much more joy.

social_posts.post_text: Glimpses from an amazing escape to Mexico. We swam in the sea, explored cenotes, drank pina coladas at a swim up bar in a cave, wandered Mayan ruins and soaked up all the sun. Grateful for another trip con mi amor.

It’s been a big week!
Most don’t know but I’ve been working behind the scenes for over a year for the shot of obtaining a license to open a cannabis dispensary in Grand Junction. A year’s worth of work on a chance. In the end, some two years after voters approved dispensaries in town, the city pushed an emergency ordinance to hold a lottery. 31 applicants were allowed into the lottery and 10 would walk away with licenses. It was a bizarre scene- 31 owners holding their breath as balls bounced around a golden bingo cage, where finally they were drawn and your destiny was read aloud.
When we reached number 10, the final ball, and 22 balls still remained and I hadn’t been chosen, my odds of winning were 4%. I assumed all hope was lost and I would have to move on. Then the final ball was chosen, and like a movie scene, my number was called. It was surreal. I let out a shout, all the media turned their cameras on me, and the interviews and celebrating began.
Now it’s time for me to get to work, and I couldn’t be more grateful for the opportunity! Also big thanks for some great photos and coverage by The Daily Sentinel and local news channels.

Some time back my brother talked me into signing up for the Dirty 30 Rides & Vibes mountain bike race. I’d planned to train for it, but life got in the way & almost no training was done. But the big day came and in all my wisdom, I decided, fuck it, I was going for it.

Now that it’s all done, BRUTAL is the first word that comes to mind. The second is EPIC. Such an amazing event & so glad my brother pushed me to join. He crushed it and finished nearly an hour before me, but with 30+ miles & 3,500 ft of elevation gain, my goal was to finish, and finish I did. And faster than I’d expected. It was a great reminder that even after all the injuries & struggles they’ve brought with them, I can still do hard shit. It may not be poetic, but knowing I could push myself both physically and mentally has been something I’ve always tied to who I was. At times it’s felt like I’ve lost that ability, so it was a great reminder there’s still some grit left in the tank. Here’s to more adventures down the road, and plenty more fun on two wheels.

Some fun snaps from the GJ Rides & Vibes race! 30 miles, 3,500’ elevation gain up some burly trails, but an absolute blast and a very well ran event. Looking forward to punishing myself again next year!
📸: @callumholloway_

Little Palisade Peach coming October 2023 🍑 Get ready for lots of adventures soon little one!
Park City, you were a treat. On to McCall for a couple days on the lake. Here we go Idaho- it’s been a while.

Just got back from some Lake Powell fun. Our family has been going here nearly every summer for about 30 years without fail. It’s a magical place with hundreds of miles of glowing sandstone canyons waiting to be explored, and spots like this waiting to be found. I’ve jumped higher spots, but I don’t know if I’ve ever found a more unique spot to jump into the abyss. It was a cave with a natural skylight from years of erosion. You could walk the arch and jump off the front, or get sendy and scramble down and jump directly through the hole. Such an amazing experience and just one of a million amazing Powell memories I carry with me.
.
#lakepowell #cliffjumping

Powell 2023.
.
#lakepowell

Headed up to The Grand Mesa chasing a meteor shower, and what a night it was! I struggled to have the timing to catch many of the big meteors, but captured lots of little ones, and one of them came through on my camera as green! Such a great weekend of staying up late under the stars, followed by waking up for hiking and paddle boarding. Forever grateful this piece of paradise is only a half hour out my back door!

The first of many to come from my little sister’s GORGEOUS wedding, captured by the incomparable @jennaleepics 

@kelsey.coleman was looking stunning at 8 months pregnant and boogied all night with me- such a trooper!

We were lucky to have Jenna shoot our wedding and I’m so happy my little sis will have the same amazing photos to immortalize her magical day.

And yes, that’s sweat on my hat… it was HOT & we got down! 🕺
This groom toss got ROWDY. Te amo cuñado.
Wild seeing all 8 Coleman siblings together in the jungle. Thanks for making it happen @aspen_chey, & thanks for throwing the party of the year! Kels & I love you & Andy to pieces!

Just got this memory from when we headed into the unknown down the Main Salmon in 2020. A week into remote central Idaho with more enthusiasm than plans.
What a magical trip it turned out to be, and what incredible friends we shared it with. I love you mi amor, and I love all the endless adventures we’ve taken together.

Surprise 9 year wedding anniversary picnic in the canyons.

14 years ago, after knowing Kels a couple months, I flew her to Colorado and brought her to my home & the canyons that held such a huge piece of my heart. They were buried in snow, but still we explored & held each other tight to stay warm.

Since that day we’ve lived a dozen lives, made homes on multiple continents, climbed peaks, sailed the seas, broken myself more times than I can count, and through it all, she’s always put the pieces back together again. She never made me question myself when I’d lost sight of who I was, and for that, I’m eternally grateful.

And now, we’re back in these canyons, ready to welcome a little boy into the world and explore these same magical glowing walls. Happy anniversary amor, & although words fall wildly short, thank you for everything.
Unaweep Canyon & Gateway… one of Colorado’s true hidden gems. Book @westworldgateway today & take this drive yourself!

This time of year is always magic in Colorado, but as I hiked through endless seas of golden Aspens with my superhero wife who could give birth to our son any day now, the changing of the seasons seemed especially remarkable.
.
It dawned on me this may be the last hike I ever take just Kels, Moch & I. And as that chapter closes, a beautiful new one begins.
.
There’s so many new experiences to come. Some we expect. Some we’ll never see coming. A new adventure. New laughs. New tears. A chance to share our love of the world with a new set of curious wide eyes.
.
I’ve set off on so many big adventures with Kels, but as this season comes to a close, I’ve never been more excited for one than I am right now.

Callum Quinn Coleman made his way into the world on October 20. At 6lbs 10oz, this little man is our biggest, most meaningful adventure yet. 

I can’t wait to explore this world with you & your mom. We’ve chased adventure, your mom and I, and it’s taken us around the globe and back. Up mountain peaks and across rough seas. But none of it compares to you.

We love you more than you know little one, and we can’t wait to see the world all over again through your eyes.
Come experience views like this with neighbors like these at our Airbnb, @westworldgateway !

Everyone told me this would be different. That something cellular changes when you look down into your little’s eyes. I listened. I thought I understood. But then you showed up. 

You smiled. Smiled sooner than you were ever supposed to. You squeezed my finger. You snuggled up beneath my chin, made it home, and made us a family.

You’re a month old today, and I promise every month going forward, I’ll be there for you little one. Every day. Every minute. I’ll be there for anything and everything.

Thank you for your snuggles. Your giggles. Thank you for making us a family.

Kels & I have always loved the holidays together. We’ve had beach day Christmases in Australia, Thailand & Nicaragua. We’ve cuddled in cozy cabins while the snow piled up outside. Some we’ve spent just the two of us. Some with friends. Others with family. But as of this holiday season, the word family has a whole new meaning for us. Looking down into those big blue eyes & hearing your little giggles fills us with love to our very core. Love for him. Love for each other. Love & gratitude for this life we’re somehow so lucky to share.
Merry Christmas & happy holidays from our little family to all of you all around the world!
.
Ps I whole heartedly expected this outing to be a disaster with a 7 week old, but he was amazing and loved every minute of it! Thanks for already being the best adventure buddy to your mom & I Callum!

Callum’s first snowshoeing trip and it was an absolute snow globe on the Mesa today! We nearly bailed because of a storm, bad roads, & if I’m being honest, cause it just sounded kind of hard with a 9 week old. But we persevered and hit the trails with my parents, and what a PERFECT day it was. Callum was amazing, not a peep as we snowshoed around frozen lakes and through sparkling forests. So grateful for this family, this amazing place we call home, and most of all, for the the little bundle of heat I had snuggled up against my belly all day. Couldn’t ask for more this holiday season. ❤️

This Costa Rican sunset was in the running up until 10/20… then this beautiful face showed up & changed everything. Love you Callum, can’t wait to explore endless beach sunsets, alpine sunrises, winding trails and so much more with you & your mom.

We headed off on our first big adventure as a family to hike, swim, sip, taste & explore all that the magical island of Kauai has to offer. It was a uniquely special trip as we got to see so many firsts for Callum, & watched as he bonded with my parents. Grateful for an amazing family & all the beauty Kauai offers those that visit.
More from the garden island. Thanks for letting us bask in all your magic Kauai.
